The paper deals with space-bounded computations, specifically the relationship between deterministic and nondeterministic logspace. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves some aspects of logic (cs.LO), information theory (cs.IT), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) in its analysis.
